1
00:00:01,213 --> 00:00:02,328
NARRATOR:
<i>Previously on</i> Angel:

2
00:00:02,493 --> 00:00:05,485
- Darla.
DARLA: We did so many terrible things.

3
00:00:05,653 --> 00:00:08,565
CORDELIA: Did you and Darla...?
ANGEL: Once. It was a dark time.

4
00:00:08,773 --> 00:00:10,729
Impossible.
Vampires can't have children.

5
00:00:10,933 --> 00:00:13,401
- We did.
WESLEY: It's human. You have a boy.

6
00:00:13,613 --> 00:00:16,002
- I'm going to have a son.
DARLA: Our baby's gonna die.

7
00:00:16,213 --> 00:00:19,603
This child, it's the one good thing
we ever did together.

8
00:00:21,093 --> 00:00:22,924
[CRYING]

9
00:00:23,133 --> 00:00:24,885
- I'm Mr. Dad.
LILAH: Daniel Holtz.

10
00:00:25,053 --> 00:00:28,284
Angel massacred his family. He spent
the rest of his life seeking revenge.

11
00:00:28,493 --> 00:00:32,042
Holtz: Go out and find others like you.
People who have suffered as we have.

12
00:00:32,253 --> 00:00:34,721
GUNN: Wes thought Angel...
FRED: Was going to kill Connor.

13
00:00:34,893 --> 00:00:36,565
LORNE:
He's taken the baby away.

14
00:00:37,533 --> 00:00:41,845
HOLTZ: I'll take care of him as my own.
- Son of a bitch! I'll never forgive you!

15
00:00:42,013 --> 00:00:44,686
You should have trusted us.
Don't come back to the hotel.

16
00:00:44,853 --> 00:00:46,969
WESLEY: If you're offering a job,
not interested.

17
00:00:47,173 --> 00:00:48,925
LILAH:
Don't think you're too good for us.

18
00:00:49,133 --> 00:00:51,203
FRED: What is it about you
that makes me melt?

19
00:00:51,413 --> 00:00:52,402
It's that I love you.

20
00:00:54,693 --> 00:00:57,127
- Connor.
JUSTINE: Don't make me do it.

21
00:00:57,333 --> 00:00:59,210
HOLTZ:
Come on, Justine.

22
00:01:01,373 --> 00:01:04,206
I sort of need to talk to you.
I'm late. I'm late.

23
00:01:04,413 --> 00:01:05,846
ANGEL:
What are you doing here?

24
00:01:07,653 --> 00:01:10,326
What you're being called to do
transcends love.

25
00:01:10,533 --> 00:01:12,489
- You've become a higher being.
- Me?

26
00:01:12,693 --> 00:01:15,412
- You murdered my father.
- I didn't. She knows it.

27
00:01:15,613 --> 00:01:18,491
Connor! Never forget that I'm your father
and that I love you.

28
00:01:18,693 --> 00:01:21,048
CORDELIA: I know somehow it's
going to be all right.

29
00:01:22,373 --> 00:01:26,525
CONNOR: You don't get to die.
You get to live forever.

30
00:01:27,773 --> 00:01:29,286
LORNE: Here you go.
FRED: Thank you.

31
00:01:29,453 --> 00:01:32,445
GUNN: You gonna eat all that?
FRED: Till I'm fat and happy.

32
00:01:32,613 --> 00:01:34,683
LORNE: These look good too.
CORDELIA: Stuffing?

33
00:01:34,853 --> 00:01:36,844
CONNOR: What's that?
CORDELIA: Sweet potatoes.

34
00:01:37,013 --> 00:01:38,765
LORNE:
Pass those over here, doll.

35
00:01:38,933 --> 00:01:40,685
CONNOR: Are they good?
CORDELIA: Try them.

36
00:01:40,853 --> 00:01:43,083
Back in Pylea, they used to
call me sweet potato.

37
00:01:43,293 --> 00:01:44,282
Really?

38
00:01:44,773 --> 00:01:47,606
Yeah, well, the exact translation
was "Fragrant Tuber," but...

39
00:01:47,813 --> 00:01:49,405
[CHUCKLING]

40
00:01:50,133 --> 00:01:51,122
You're not hungry?

41
00:01:52,173 --> 00:01:54,129
No, I'm starving. I just...

42
00:01:54,293 --> 00:01:55,567
I wanna freeze this moment.

43
00:01:56,653 --> 00:01:58,928
You. Connor.

44
00:02:00,653 --> 00:02:01,642
All of us.

45
00:02:01,813 --> 00:02:06,329
Safe and happy and together.

46
00:02:08,293 --> 00:02:10,523
Considering what we went through
over this summer.

47
00:02:14,933 --> 00:02:16,446
To family.

48
00:02:18,893 --> 00:02:19,882
To family.

49
00:02:21,613 --> 00:02:22,807
As long as it's not mine.

50
00:02:22,973 --> 00:02:25,248
[CHUCKLING]

51
00:02:27,173 --> 00:02:28,811
You can't toast with an empty glass.

52
00:02:29,013 --> 00:02:31,447
- It's not bad luck, is it?
- Angel, relax.

53
00:02:31,613 --> 00:02:33,490
Things are back
to the way they should be...

54
00:02:33,653 --> 00:02:36,042
...and nothing is ever
going to break us apart again.

55
00:02:37,133 --> 00:02:38,486
And if anything tries...

56
00:02:38,693 --> 00:02:42,447
...I'm going to have to go all glowy
and personally kick its ass.

57
00:02:42,653 --> 00:02:44,245
I like it when you glow.

58
00:02:44,413 --> 00:02:46,244
Well, play your cards right...

59
00:02:46,413 --> 00:02:48,449
CONNOR:
Do I have to watch this part?

60
00:02:50,053 --> 00:02:51,611
I could poke your eyes out.

61
00:02:51,933 --> 00:02:53,764
Come on, Dad.
It'll stick up like yours.

62
00:02:53,973 --> 00:02:56,089
You should be so lucky. Let's eat.

63
00:02:57,133 --> 00:02:58,122
FRED: Rolls?
LORNE: Hmm.

64
00:02:58,933 --> 00:03:00,491
Those look good.

65
00:03:01,653 --> 00:03:04,725
CORDELIA: Careful, those are hot.
GUNN: Now we're talking.

66
00:03:04,893 --> 00:03:06,963
CONNOR: I like this.
CORDELIA: I thought so.

67
00:03:07,133 --> 00:03:09,044
- Can I get the...?
CONNOR: Delicious.

68
00:03:09,253 --> 00:03:10,527
- Carrots.
FRED: Smells so good.

69
00:03:10,693 --> 00:03:13,685
GUNN: Get your hands out of my plate.
FRED: Peas?

70
00:03:14,053 --> 00:03:16,567
CONNOR: Can I have the rolls?
WESLEY: The salt, please.

71
00:03:16,773 --> 00:03:18,968
FRED: Kill me now
before my stomach explodes.

72
00:03:20,053 --> 00:03:22,408
CORDELIA: Try the gravy.
- It comes in a little boat.

73
00:03:24,493 --> 00:03:26,006
Could I get the...?

74
00:03:31,133 --> 00:03:32,646
Cordy, what...?

75
00:03:37,333 --> 00:03:38,971
Now look what you've done, silly.

76
00:03:47,093 --> 00:03:51,644
Freeze the moment, Dad.
It'll last forever.

77
00:04:09,253 --> 00:04:11,642
Deep Down

78
00:05:06,653 --> 00:05:08,245
[GUNN GASPING]

79
00:05:08,453 --> 00:05:10,444
GUNN: You okay?
- No. You?

80
00:05:10,613 --> 00:05:13,685
- Nope.
- Nice we still do things together.

81
00:05:16,413 --> 00:05:17,562
How we doing?

82
00:05:18,693 --> 00:05:19,762
About the same.

83
00:05:20,413 --> 00:05:21,528
[FRED SCREAMS]

84
00:05:22,853 --> 00:05:23,842
FRED:
Charles!

85
00:05:26,533 --> 00:05:27,522
Hang on.

86
00:05:32,133 --> 00:05:33,168
[GROWLING]

87
00:05:35,573 --> 00:05:39,009
GUNN: Your ass better be insured.
- Worry about your own ass, <i>ese</i>.

88
00:05:39,693 --> 00:05:43,572
Warm bloods rolling down my street
hassling my <i>hermanos</i>. It ain't gonna fly.

89
00:05:43,733 --> 00:05:46,372
- We're looking for the girl.
GUNN: Tell us where she is.

90
00:05:46,533 --> 00:05:47,602
Who, Marissa?

91
00:05:47,813 --> 00:05:50,646
I thought you guys were supposed
to be a couple detectives.

92
00:05:51,173 --> 00:05:53,448
Or was that before your buddy Angel
went bye-bye?

93
00:05:53,653 --> 00:05:56,121
- We found you, didn't we?
- And look what it got you.

94
00:05:58,133 --> 00:06:01,045
We just want to talk to her, that's all.

95
00:06:01,813 --> 00:06:04,168
Condemned building off Figueroa.
Top floor.

96
00:06:04,973 --> 00:06:06,884
And tell her I want my CDs back, yeah?

97
00:06:07,093 --> 00:06:09,812
GUNN: We'll pass it along.
- No, you know what? Better yet...

98
00:06:11,093 --> 00:06:12,492
...I'll tell her myself.

99
00:06:12,773 --> 00:06:13,888
[GROWLING]

100
00:06:20,613 --> 00:06:21,966
Angel left you a little toy?

101
00:06:22,893 --> 00:06:23,962
More than one.

102
00:06:28,693 --> 00:06:29,682
Charles!

103
00:06:31,973 --> 00:06:34,248
[SCREAMING AND GROANING]

104
00:06:36,613 --> 00:06:38,410
[GRUNTS]

105
00:06:52,213 --> 00:06:53,248
Did you see that?

106
00:06:55,653 --> 00:06:57,371
Wasn't that cool?

107
00:06:58,053 --> 00:06:59,406
[CONNOR CHUCKLES]

108
00:06:59,573 --> 00:07:00,847
That was cool.

109
00:07:04,893 --> 00:07:07,851
FRED: You can't run off like that when
we're supposed to be working.

110
00:07:08,013 --> 00:07:09,128
We've talked about that.

111
00:07:09,293 --> 00:07:11,204
- Their gang was getting away.
GUNN: Let them.

112
00:07:11,373 --> 00:07:13,284
What you don't do
is divide your strength.

113
00:07:14,573 --> 00:07:16,689
- Sorry.
FRED: It was different in Quor-toth...

114
00:07:16,853 --> 00:07:20,004
...but you're in Los Angeles now.
You're taking on a big responsibility.

115
00:07:20,173 --> 00:07:22,767
You have to start thinking
about more than just yourself.

116
00:07:22,973 --> 00:07:24,167
I know.

117
00:07:24,933 --> 00:07:25,922
I know.

118
00:07:29,333 --> 00:07:31,642
That thing with the axe was cool, huh?

119
00:07:33,773 --> 00:07:35,286
Yeah, that was tight.

120
00:07:36,093 --> 00:07:37,208
Now you get to clean it.

121
00:07:37,373 --> 00:07:40,092
- Vamp's dust. Nothing to clean.
- Two coats of polish.

122
00:07:48,893 --> 00:07:50,611
We gonna tell him?

123
00:07:51,133 --> 00:07:54,205
- I don't wanna get his hopes up again.
- What about yours?

124
00:07:55,293 --> 00:07:56,487
We have to keep trying.

125
00:07:56,693 --> 00:07:59,765
I'm not saying we shouldn't,
but we spent the last three months...

126
00:07:59,933 --> 00:08:02,493
...chasing dead ends
trying to find Angel and Cordy...

127
00:08:02,653 --> 00:08:05,372
...and the only thing
we're closing in on is an eviction.

128
00:08:05,573 --> 00:08:08,565
It'd be a lot easier handling this crap
with Lorne pitching in.

129
00:08:08,733 --> 00:08:11,042
Where's our future-reading empath
when we need him?

130
00:08:11,253 --> 00:08:13,813
Mr. Big-Hit is too busy
"Danke Schoen"-ing tourists...

131
00:08:13,973 --> 00:08:14,962
...to care about us.

132
00:08:15,173 --> 00:08:17,846
- You try him again?
- Like, 60 times.

133
00:08:18,013 --> 00:08:19,366
He's lost the mission, bro.

134
00:08:19,573 --> 00:08:23,248
We're about to lose this whole place,
and you know you can't say "bro."

135
00:08:23,413 --> 00:08:25,722
We need to start hustling up
some paying clients.

136
00:08:25,933 --> 00:08:28,606
We will, as soon as we find Marissa.

137
00:08:28,773 --> 00:08:29,842
Can I say "dog"?

138
00:08:32,373 --> 00:08:33,362
Oh, this looks good.

139
00:08:33,773 --> 00:08:36,731
"Condemned tenement on Figueroa."
Could be her.

140
00:08:36,933 --> 00:08:38,730
Evil Dead was probably messing with us.

141
00:08:38,893 --> 00:08:40,963
Not much chance she knows anything.

142
00:08:41,133 --> 00:08:44,523
Angel's car was found by the bluffs.
That used to be her feeding ground.

143
00:08:44,693 --> 00:08:46,649
She might be able to tell us
what happened...

144
00:08:46,813 --> 00:08:49,202
...if we can find her.
CONNOR: Find who?

145
00:09:04,253 --> 00:09:05,686
ANGEL:
Cordelia.

146
00:09:07,653 --> 00:09:10,804
- I didn't think you were coming.
- You know me better than that.

147
00:09:11,733 --> 00:09:12,882
Better than anybody.

148
00:09:13,093 --> 00:09:14,572
[CHUCKLING]

149
00:09:14,733 --> 00:09:16,086
I don't know if that's true.

150
00:09:16,813 --> 00:09:19,327
Yes, you do.

151
00:09:22,133 --> 00:09:24,601
It's so beautiful here.

152
00:09:25,973 --> 00:09:27,326
ANGEL:
Yes.

153
00:09:27,493 --> 00:09:28,642
Yes, it is.

154
00:09:31,293 --> 00:09:33,409
Just the way it should be.

155
00:09:38,133 --> 00:09:39,452
But it's not.

156
00:09:40,133 --> 00:09:41,725
This isn't how it happened.

157
00:09:42,613 --> 00:09:44,285
I know.

158
00:09:45,093 --> 00:09:46,970
I like this version better.

159
00:09:47,173 --> 00:09:48,162
It was Connor.

160
00:09:49,093 --> 00:09:51,163
He was here. He...

161
00:09:57,293 --> 00:10:00,365
I can't remember what it was like...

162
00:10:00,533 --> 00:10:02,171
...not knowing you.

163
00:10:02,853 --> 00:10:04,730
Not being close to you.

164
00:10:06,853 --> 00:10:09,413
I'm in love with you, Angel.

165
00:10:09,813 --> 00:10:12,964
Deep down, I think I have been
for a long time.

166
00:10:13,733 --> 00:10:15,405
I needed you to know that.

167
00:10:24,893 --> 00:10:26,690
I need you, Cordy.

168
00:10:27,293 --> 00:10:28,282
I need you.

169
00:10:29,333 --> 00:10:30,527
[ANGEL BITES]

170
00:10:32,053 --> 00:10:33,884
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

171
00:10:34,053 --> 00:10:35,042
[CORDELIA SCREAMING]

172
00:10:35,253 --> 00:10:36,572
[SCREAMS]

173
00:10:40,813 --> 00:10:42,326
So why didn't you tell me?

174
00:10:42,773 --> 00:10:43,967
We wanted to be sure.

175
00:10:44,133 --> 00:10:45,964
We don't even know
if Marissa saw anything.

176
00:10:46,173 --> 00:10:47,686
- But she could have.
FRED: Maybe.

177
00:10:47,853 --> 00:10:49,571
We're gonna talk to her and find out.

178
00:10:49,773 --> 00:10:50,967
- I'm coming.
GUNN: No.

179
00:10:51,573 --> 00:10:54,292
- It's only one vamp. We can handle it.
- He's my father.

180
00:10:54,693 --> 00:10:57,207
If she knows what happened to him, l...

181
00:10:59,373 --> 00:11:01,728
Okay. Go get your weapons.

182
00:11:06,373 --> 00:11:08,762
- Think that's a good idea?
- I'll keep an eye on him.

183
00:11:08,933 --> 00:11:12,084
Getting information is a finesse job.
He's a blunt instrument.

184
00:11:12,253 --> 00:11:14,642
You wanna tell him no?
You saw how much he's hurting.

185
00:11:14,813 --> 00:11:18,044
How do you think he'll feel if all
Vampirella saw was sand and seaweed?

186
00:11:18,213 --> 00:11:20,647
This is it. No Angel, no Cordy.
We can't find Holtz...

187
00:11:20,813 --> 00:11:22,644
...his psycho girlfriend's gone.
Nothing.

188
00:11:22,813 --> 00:11:26,522
- There's still Wolfram and Hart.
- We'll stroll into their guarded offices...

189
00:11:26,693 --> 00:11:30,322
...and ask Lilah for help finding out
what happened to their archenemy.

190
00:11:30,493 --> 00:11:32,563
But we're broke,
so it'll have to be pro bono.

191
00:11:32,773 --> 00:11:34,365
I didn't say it would be easy.

192
00:11:34,573 --> 00:11:36,131
How's "impossible"?

193
00:11:36,293 --> 00:11:37,328
They're too big.

194
00:11:37,533 --> 00:11:39,842
Without Angel here, we can't afford
to piss them off.

195
00:11:40,373 --> 00:11:42,409
- Maybe we should think about asking...
- No.

196
00:11:45,133 --> 00:11:47,010
Well, I'm glad we talked it over.

197
00:11:47,213 --> 00:11:49,807
- We already asked him for help twice.
- We'll ask him again.

198
00:11:50,013 --> 00:11:51,651
Wesley doesn't give a damn about us.

199
00:11:52,133 --> 00:11:53,691
Have we given him a reason to?

200
00:11:54,613 --> 00:11:56,569
He's made his choice.

201
00:11:57,253 --> 00:11:58,971
Now he has to live with it.

202
00:12:02,053 --> 00:12:04,328
[MOANING]

203
00:12:06,333 --> 00:12:08,483
That didn't suck.

204
00:12:10,373 --> 00:12:13,570
Well, maybe just a little bit.

205
00:12:16,093 --> 00:12:19,130
Perhaps that's something
we can expand on next time.

206
00:12:21,133 --> 00:12:23,727
What makes you think
there will be a next time?

207
00:12:25,373 --> 00:12:27,887
Because you can't resist me.

208
00:12:30,733 --> 00:12:33,691
I think you have that backwards.

209
00:12:36,053 --> 00:12:37,327
Where are you going?

210
00:12:37,733 --> 00:12:40,406
Snack break's over.
Time to get back to work.

211
00:12:40,573 --> 00:12:43,485
And Wolfram and Hart
does its best work after dark.

212
00:12:43,653 --> 00:12:46,929
The sun's bad for your complexion.
Ask Angel.

213
00:12:47,093 --> 00:12:48,526
Oh, right, you can't...

214
00:12:48,693 --> 00:12:51,765
...because of the whole "wanting
to smother you with a pillow" thing.

215
00:12:51,973 --> 00:12:55,170
Wouldn't think kidnapping his son
would have such a negative effect.

216
00:12:55,333 --> 00:12:57,608
You thought you were doing
the right thing.

217
00:12:57,773 --> 00:13:00,082
I hear that can be confusing.

218
00:13:01,773 --> 00:13:03,445
Have you tried talking to him?

219
00:13:03,653 --> 00:13:05,291
Maybe when he gets back you could...

220
00:13:05,453 --> 00:13:06,602
[CHUCKLING]

221
00:13:07,693 --> 00:13:08,682
What?

222
00:13:08,853 --> 00:13:13,005
I have no idea where Angel is,
Lilah, or what happened to him.

223
00:13:14,533 --> 00:13:16,205
And I really couldn't care.

224
00:13:16,573 --> 00:13:19,770
Wow. That was cold.

225
00:13:22,173 --> 00:13:25,085
I think we're finally making progress.

226
00:13:28,893 --> 00:13:33,683
Come on. Doesn't it bother you
just a little bit, the not knowing?

227
00:13:33,853 --> 00:13:35,844
That part of my life is dead.

228
00:13:38,653 --> 00:13:40,245
It doesn't concern me now.

229
00:13:42,893 --> 00:13:45,009
No, it doesn't.

230
00:14:19,573 --> 00:14:20,562
It's time.

231
00:14:24,693 --> 00:14:26,331
Let's go for a boat ride.

232
00:14:39,893 --> 00:14:42,248
JUSTINE:
So, what's it gonna be tonight, captain?

233
00:14:42,413 --> 00:14:47,168
Bicycle? Old tire?
Or maybe we'll get real lucky...

234
00:14:47,333 --> 00:14:49,563
...and catch us a nice shopping cart.

235
00:14:50,613 --> 00:14:52,046
Here's a wacky thought.

236
00:14:52,213 --> 00:14:54,443
Why don't you swim
down there yourself?

237
00:14:56,013 --> 00:14:57,128
[BEEPING]

238
00:14:57,293 --> 00:14:59,602
No contact. We'll try the next grid.

239
00:15:03,053 --> 00:15:05,692
Do you really think finding Angel's
gonna change anything?

240
00:15:06,093 --> 00:15:07,651
Everything changes.

241
00:15:07,813 --> 00:15:10,373
I guess anything's better
than sitting around in my cage...

242
00:15:10,533 --> 00:15:12,569
...with nothing to do
but to fill my bucket.

243
00:15:12,773 --> 00:15:15,890
Perhaps you should've considered
that before slitting my throat.

244
00:15:16,333 --> 00:15:18,608
The great Wesley Wyndam-Pryce.

245
00:15:18,773 --> 00:15:22,004
The shining beacon
of all that's good and pure.

246
00:15:22,213 --> 00:15:25,205
But, wait, no.
That's before he started...

247
00:15:25,373 --> 00:15:28,604
...banging the enemy and keeping
the slave girl in his closet.

248
00:15:28,813 --> 00:15:32,408
You were always a slave, Justine.
You just couldn't see the chains.

249
00:15:33,253 --> 00:15:36,723
Thanks, swami. I'll meditate on that.

250
00:15:37,653 --> 00:15:39,132
You think she'd be disappointed?

251
00:15:40,773 --> 00:15:41,762
Who?

252
00:15:42,093 --> 00:15:43,412
Your sister.

253
00:15:44,773 --> 00:15:46,604
That's where it all began, isn't it?

254
00:15:46,893 --> 00:15:50,090
Sister murdered by a vampire.
Consumed with the need for revenge.

255
00:15:50,293 --> 00:15:52,363
- For justice.
- Is that what you call it?

256
00:15:52,533 --> 00:15:54,205
Turning a son against his father?

257
00:15:54,413 --> 00:15:56,449
Angel got what he deserved.

258
00:15:57,173 --> 00:15:59,482
We all get what we deserve.

259
00:16:00,213 --> 00:16:02,124
You and Holtz deserved each other.

260
00:16:02,733 --> 00:16:04,883
You two have so much in common.

261
00:16:05,093 --> 00:16:10,167
Pain, loss. Deep-seated lack
of anything approaching humor.

262
00:16:10,333 --> 00:16:13,086
I don't know. We had a few laughs.

263
00:16:13,293 --> 00:16:15,853
Getting you to steal Angel's baby,
that was a good one.

264
00:16:16,013 --> 00:16:19,369
Better than tricking Connor into sinking
his father to the bottom of the ocean?

265
00:16:19,573 --> 00:16:21,643
Well, that was worth a
couple of yuks too.

266
00:16:22,893 --> 00:16:24,645
Not much of a plan though,
was it, really?

267
00:16:24,853 --> 00:16:28,209
Easy to figure out which door
to kick in when Angel went missing.

268
00:16:28,373 --> 00:16:30,364
And not much harder
to persuade you...

269
00:16:30,533 --> 00:16:33,047
...to betray everything Holtz
had given his life for.

270
00:16:33,533 --> 00:16:35,285
Not that it was worth very much.

271
00:16:35,493 --> 00:16:38,405
But you should know.
You're the one that ended it.

272
00:16:39,533 --> 00:16:41,524
I'll take away your bucket.

273
00:16:55,013 --> 00:16:56,412
Or we could do it the loud way.

274
00:16:59,493 --> 00:17:02,451
It doesn't matter.
Looks like she's out.

275
00:17:03,093 --> 00:17:06,165
Man, that's just nasty.
I don't know how people live like this.

276
00:17:06,333 --> 00:17:07,448
FRED:
Helps to be dead.

277
00:17:08,053 --> 00:17:11,602
- One more reason to stay pink and rosy.
- Word.

278
00:17:13,293 --> 00:17:15,204
So, what do you think?

279
00:17:15,373 --> 00:17:18,410
From the smell, I'm guessing
she still lives here. Should we wait...

280
00:17:18,573 --> 00:17:20,291
...for her to come back or...?
- No.

281
00:17:21,973 --> 00:17:24,726
[MUSIC PLAYS]

282
00:17:25,573 --> 00:17:26,892
We won't have to.

283
00:17:37,293 --> 00:17:39,602
FRED:
Marissa, stop. We just want to talk.

284
00:17:39,813 --> 00:17:41,610
- I don't know anything.
GUNN: You psychic?

285
00:17:41,773 --> 00:17:43,604
MARISSA: No.
- Then let us ask a question.

286
00:17:43,773 --> 00:17:45,843
- You know the bluffs by the beach?
- No.

287
00:17:46,053 --> 00:17:47,281
You used to feed there.

288
00:17:48,453 --> 00:17:49,442
Those bluffs.

289
00:17:49,613 --> 00:17:51,968
Three months ago a friend
of ours went missing there.

290
00:17:52,173 --> 00:17:55,210
Tall? Good-Looking? Weird hair?

291
00:17:55,413 --> 00:17:57,051
FRED:
You saw him?

292
00:17:57,253 --> 00:18:00,211
I see a lot of things.
What do you care?

293
00:18:00,373 --> 00:18:02,409
He's my father. If you know...

294
00:18:02,693 --> 00:18:03,967
[CONNOR SCREAMS]

295
00:18:06,853 --> 00:18:08,764
You never let your guard down!

296
00:18:09,373 --> 00:18:10,442
FRED:
Connor!

297
00:18:15,013 --> 00:18:17,163
If he ain't dead, I'm gonna kill him.

298
00:18:37,373 --> 00:18:38,408
What did you see?

299
00:18:38,613 --> 00:18:41,286
Look, whatever I saw,
whatever I didn't see...

300
00:18:41,453 --> 00:18:43,489
...it doesn't matter, okay?

301
00:18:45,173 --> 00:18:46,731
Come on, handsome.

302
00:18:51,613 --> 00:18:53,524
It'll be our little secret.

303
00:18:57,493 --> 00:18:58,482
GUNN:
Connor?

304
00:19:05,413 --> 00:19:06,402
Connor!

305
00:19:09,533 --> 00:19:11,046
FRED: You all right?
- Where is she?

306
00:19:11,213 --> 00:19:14,250
She attacked me. I had no choice.

307
00:19:15,573 --> 00:19:17,848
Maybe you would have
if you weren't playing hero.

308
00:19:18,013 --> 00:19:19,810
Do you know
what you just did?

309
00:19:21,533 --> 00:19:22,727
[CLATTERING]

310
00:19:23,053 --> 00:19:24,042
Connor!

311
00:19:30,333 --> 00:19:32,324
Three months of this
and he dusts our lead.

312
00:19:32,533 --> 00:19:35,127
You know he wants to find Angel.
How do you think he feels?

313
00:19:35,333 --> 00:19:36,766
It's not like he talks to me.

314
00:19:36,973 --> 00:19:40,124
After everything he's gone through,
you need to be a bit more patient.

315
00:19:40,333 --> 00:19:41,527
He's just a boy.

316
00:19:41,693 --> 00:19:44,446
You sure about that?
Offspring of two vampires?

317
00:19:44,653 --> 00:19:46,689
Last I checked,
that's not supposed to happen.

318
00:19:46,893 --> 00:19:49,646
And jumping off a six-story
without busting your coconut...

319
00:19:49,813 --> 00:19:52,327
...kind of sways me to the side
of "not just a boy."

320
00:19:52,533 --> 00:19:55,684
Come on, Fred. His nickname
back in Quor-toth was "the Destroyer."

321
00:19:55,893 --> 00:19:58,965
Unless you put "Conan"
in front of that, it's not a good sign.

322
00:20:00,453 --> 00:20:04,412
He's Angel's son.
That's all that matters.

323
00:20:08,333 --> 00:20:09,402
[SIGHS]

324
00:20:23,653 --> 00:20:24,768
ANGEL:
Beautiful, isn't it?

325
00:20:26,733 --> 00:20:28,246
The way it should be.

326
00:20:30,133 --> 00:20:32,169
What, no hug?

327
00:20:34,733 --> 00:20:36,166
Just get it over with.

328
00:20:36,373 --> 00:20:38,933
What's the rush?
I'm not going anywhere.

329
00:20:39,093 --> 00:20:40,128
CONNOR:
No, you're not.

330
00:20:47,773 --> 00:20:49,889
[CHUCKLING]

331
00:20:50,853 --> 00:20:52,081
What are you laughing at?

332
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:53,402
I'll tell you later.

333
00:20:53,733 --> 00:20:55,485
[GROWLING]

334
00:20:56,333 --> 00:20:57,812
[GRUNTING AND GROANING]

335
00:21:22,693 --> 00:21:24,285
Dad!

336
00:21:28,973 --> 00:21:29,962
[SCREAMS]

337
00:21:31,653 --> 00:21:33,564
[CHUCKLING]

338
00:21:35,653 --> 00:21:36,642
Thanks.

339
00:21:39,053 --> 00:21:41,203
[SCREAMING]

340
00:21:43,613 --> 00:21:45,365
[MUSIC PLAYS]

341
00:21:45,733 --> 00:21:48,293
Go easy, Mabel. Remember,
they're paying to see the green.

342
00:21:48,853 --> 00:21:51,003
- Two minutes.
- Thanks, sweetie.

343
00:21:51,213 --> 00:21:52,202
<i>Bon soir</i>.

344
00:21:52,373 --> 00:21:58,482
Lorne? Lorne! Hey, it's Fred.
I've been trying to get a hold of you.

345
00:21:58,693 --> 00:22:01,605
I'm sorry, hon. I've been booked
out the "wa" and past the "zoo."

346
00:22:01,773 --> 00:22:04,003
If I get any hotter they'll
have to stamp me out.

347
00:22:04,173 --> 00:22:07,131
Lorne, I know you're busy,
but we really need your help.

348
00:22:07,293 --> 00:22:10,603
We had a lead, but it, uh...

349
00:22:10,773 --> 00:22:14,482
...kind of died.
Did you talk to your connections?

350
00:22:14,693 --> 00:22:16,445
<i>Have they heard anything about Angel?</i>

351
00:22:16,613 --> 00:22:19,730
Not a peep. But if I Miracle-Ear anything
I'll send up a smoke signal.

352
00:22:20,493 --> 00:22:23,132
That's my cue.
Take care of yourself...

353
00:22:23,293 --> 00:22:26,012
...and make sure Fluffy's
getting enough love.

354
00:22:26,733 --> 00:22:27,722
Lorne?

355
00:22:29,853 --> 00:22:31,650
GUNN: He have anything?
- No.

356
00:22:32,093 --> 00:22:35,005
And who's Fluffy?
Are you Fluffy?

357
00:22:35,213 --> 00:22:37,727
- He called me Fluffy?
- He said, "Make sure..."

358
00:22:38,133 --> 00:22:40,283
Wait. You don't think
he was referring...

359
00:22:40,453 --> 00:22:42,728
...to anything of mine
that's fluffy, do you?

360
00:22:42,893 --> 00:22:45,566
Because that would
just be inappropriate.

361
00:22:45,733 --> 00:22:49,692
Like deserting us? No leads, no clients.

362
00:22:49,853 --> 00:22:52,890
Pretty soon, no roof
over my smooth, delicate head.

363
00:22:53,893 --> 00:22:55,804
I could make you a paper hat.

364
00:22:58,693 --> 00:23:00,206
It's going to be okay.

365
00:23:00,373 --> 00:23:02,603
Angel and Cordy are out there
somewhere.

366
00:23:02,773 --> 00:23:04,604
No matter what
the Powers-That-Screw-You...

367
00:23:04,773 --> 00:23:08,163
...throw at us, we're going to find them.

368
00:23:10,253 --> 00:23:11,242
LILAH:
You found Angel?

369
00:23:11,453 --> 00:23:14,126
Young Gavin's had a breakthrough
with the psychics.

370
00:23:14,693 --> 00:23:17,526
Brain boys finally earning their keep.
So where is he?

371
00:23:17,693 --> 00:23:19,809
They haven't pinpointed
his exact location yet.

372
00:23:19,973 --> 00:23:22,692
But they have ascertained that he's
safe and immobilized.

373
00:23:22,853 --> 00:23:25,811
Really? Maybe you can lead them
in a rousing chant...

374
00:23:25,973 --> 00:23:28,851
...and get them to muster up
a little more vague.

375
00:23:29,013 --> 00:23:32,403
He's contained and out of play,
which suits our purposes just fine.

376
00:23:32,613 --> 00:23:35,605
If our purpose is to get caught
with our prophesies down.

377
00:23:35,773 --> 00:23:38,571
Angel is supposed to be a major
player in the Apocalypse.

378
00:23:38,773 --> 00:23:40,843
The little pet project
the senior partners...

379
00:23:41,013 --> 00:23:43,481
...have been working on
since the beginning of time.

380
00:23:43,693 --> 00:23:46,810
Three months, and all you've
been able to ferret out is nothing.

381
00:23:46,973 --> 00:23:51,922
Lilah, Gavin's work with the psychics
has uncovered some invaluable intel...

382
00:23:52,413 --> 00:23:54,973
...in a variety of unexpected areas.

383
00:23:58,253 --> 00:23:59,652
Care to enlighten us?

384
00:24:00,613 --> 00:24:04,891
What I do in my personal time
is none of Gavin's business.

385
00:24:05,093 --> 00:24:06,492
But everything's my business.

386
00:24:08,813 --> 00:24:11,088
I'm not sleeping with him
for information.

387
00:24:11,853 --> 00:24:14,242
Please don't tell me it's the chiseled jaw.

388
00:24:14,933 --> 00:24:18,642
If you have his confidence,
we can play it to our advantage.

389
00:24:19,653 --> 00:24:24,568
He doesn't know anything.
There's nothing to take advantage of.

390
00:24:24,853 --> 00:24:25,842
Except you.

391
00:24:26,773 --> 00:24:28,570
[ELEVATOR PINGS]

392
00:24:29,253 --> 00:24:33,087
Staff meeting in an hour.
Don't be late. Gavin.

393
00:24:40,293 --> 00:24:42,090
[BEEPING]

394
00:24:44,373 --> 00:24:47,251
Solid contact. Definitely metallic.

395
00:24:47,413 --> 00:24:50,644
Probably more junk.
Could be anything down there.

396
00:24:52,093 --> 00:24:53,572
Better have a look, then.

397
00:25:38,973 --> 00:25:40,167
WESLEY:
Justine.

398
00:25:42,493 --> 00:25:44,324
Come on.

399
00:25:44,893 --> 00:25:47,361
[GRUNTING]

400
00:25:55,053 --> 00:25:57,931
Congratulations. You're the big hero.

401
00:25:59,093 --> 00:26:02,449
Your friends will throw you a party.
I wonder what the cake's gonna look...

402
00:26:37,893 --> 00:26:39,451
Blood?

403
00:26:39,813 --> 00:26:40,882
WESLEY:
Animal.

404
00:26:41,893 --> 00:26:43,884
JUSTINE: Why hurry?
He's not going anywhere.

405
00:26:44,053 --> 00:26:46,647
WESLEY: A vampire can exist
indefinitely without feeding.

406
00:26:46,813 --> 00:26:49,930
But the damage to brain function
from starvation can be catastrophic.

407
00:26:52,653 --> 00:26:53,722
Slowly.

408
00:26:54,053 --> 00:26:57,443
All your energy wasted to save
that thing. For what?

409
00:26:57,893 --> 00:26:59,008
A happy ending?

410
00:26:59,173 --> 00:27:00,811
Everything like it was?

411
00:27:01,013 --> 00:27:02,571
He hates you.

412
00:27:03,253 --> 00:27:04,606
They all do.

413
00:27:04,773 --> 00:27:07,333
And they're never going to
take you back.

414
00:27:17,013 --> 00:27:20,483
- This going to be the yelling thing again?
- No, no yelling.

415
00:27:21,693 --> 00:27:23,809
- He looks like he's going to yell.
- I do not.

416
00:27:24,013 --> 00:27:26,243
- He always looks like he is.
- I'm not gonna yell.

417
00:27:26,413 --> 00:27:29,405
- Where have you been?
- Out.

418
00:27:30,413 --> 00:27:31,812
We were worried.

419
00:27:37,613 --> 00:27:38,602
I'm sorry.

420
00:27:40,693 --> 00:27:44,481
I shouldn't run off alone.
You'd think I'd know that by now.

421
00:27:44,653 --> 00:27:46,803
It's that big, thick melon.

422
00:27:47,013 --> 00:27:49,402
Your dad's got one just like it.

423
00:27:49,573 --> 00:27:51,803
Angel's always flying off,
getting into trouble.

424
00:27:52,013 --> 00:27:54,208
- I'm not like him.
- You're not as strong yet, but...

425
00:27:54,373 --> 00:27:56,329
Like I care what you think?

426
00:27:56,693 --> 00:27:58,285
What'd you say?

427
00:27:58,453 --> 00:28:01,365
It's been a long night.
Why don't you go wash up.

428
00:28:04,053 --> 00:28:05,042
I'm fine.

429
00:28:10,893 --> 00:28:13,726
I try to be nice, and you see
what he does? He keeps pushing.

430
00:28:13,893 --> 00:28:16,088
It's like... It's like he wants
me to lose it.

431
00:28:16,293 --> 00:28:19,683
He's testing you. With Angel gone,
you're the alpha male.

432
00:28:19,893 --> 00:28:21,485
Damn straight.

433
00:28:22,173 --> 00:28:26,166
- Don't let it go to your head.
- That's not the direction it's flowing.

434
00:28:28,373 --> 00:28:30,011
[PHONE RINGING]

435
00:28:33,333 --> 00:28:34,482
Let it ring.

436
00:28:34,653 --> 00:28:36,609
What if it's a client?

437
00:28:38,533 --> 00:28:41,172
Then the big dog better close the deal.

438
00:28:44,413 --> 00:28:45,687
Angel Investigations.

439
00:28:46,933 --> 00:28:48,332
Why is it like this?

440
00:28:48,733 --> 00:28:51,088
LORNE:
That's the age-old, bubby.

441
00:28:51,253 --> 00:28:53,767
I'll fire you off a postcard
if I noodle an answer.

442
00:28:54,733 --> 00:28:57,293
Life should be beautiful and bright.

443
00:28:57,493 --> 00:29:00,246
But no matter how hard I try...

444
00:29:01,973 --> 00:29:05,807
...everything I touch turns to ashes.

445
00:29:06,373 --> 00:29:08,728
There goes that encouraging hug
I was planning.

446
00:29:08,933 --> 00:29:10,127
Snap to, buckaroo.

447
00:29:10,293 --> 00:29:13,603
The only one turning to ashes
is that patricidal pup of yours.

448
00:29:13,773 --> 00:29:17,368
Hell, I'd take him on myself
if I wasn't just a crappy hallucination.

449
00:29:20,053 --> 00:29:21,884
WESLEY: How is he?
- How do you think?

450
00:29:22,093 --> 00:29:24,891
- He won't shut up.
ANGEL: I have to stop him.

451
00:29:25,053 --> 00:29:27,567
You want to bitch-slap sourpuss
over there for practice?

452
00:29:27,733 --> 00:29:28,927
I'm your cheering section.

453
00:29:29,133 --> 00:29:30,327
Angel.

454
00:29:30,533 --> 00:29:31,761
I have to do it.

455
00:29:32,253 --> 00:29:34,892
Shh. You need to rest now.

456
00:29:47,093 --> 00:29:49,004
I should've killed you.

457
00:29:50,413 --> 00:29:51,732
[JUSTINE CHUCKLES]

458
00:29:52,133 --> 00:29:54,169
And me without my camera.

459
00:29:54,373 --> 00:29:57,843
He's been down there too long.
Pig's blood isn't enough.

460
00:29:58,053 --> 00:30:00,487
- He needs more substantial nourishment.
- Like what?

461
00:30:02,533 --> 00:30:05,331
Screw you.
I'm not feeding that thing.

462
00:30:05,493 --> 00:30:08,929
No. Your blood's too thin.

463
00:30:30,973 --> 00:30:33,771
[MUMBLING]

464
00:30:37,093 --> 00:30:39,926
LINWOOD: We've got a lot of
ground to cover, so let's get to it.

465
00:30:40,093 --> 00:30:42,004
But first, let's talk about Lilah.

466
00:30:42,453 --> 00:30:44,762
Everybody had a chance
to review her file?

467
00:30:45,893 --> 00:30:48,168
Good. Recommendations?

468
00:30:48,373 --> 00:30:50,841
If I could just have a few minutes
to explain.

469
00:30:51,053 --> 00:30:52,645
Your record speaks for itself.

470
00:30:52,853 --> 00:30:55,492
Volumes.
Your failures at Wolfram and Hart...

471
00:30:55,653 --> 00:30:59,168
...outstrip your successes
by an uncomfortable margin.

472
00:30:59,373 --> 00:31:02,251
Perhaps you would fare better
at a less central office.

473
00:31:02,413 --> 00:31:04,165
One of the third-world
dimensions maybe.

474
00:31:04,693 --> 00:31:07,082
- Sorry.
- What was that?

475
00:31:07,613 --> 00:31:09,569
I said, I'm sorry.

476
00:31:09,773 --> 00:31:15,405
I've made mistakes.
But fear was never one of them.

477
00:31:16,893 --> 00:31:18,690
Is there something you'd like to share?

478
00:31:18,893 --> 00:31:22,090
Why haven't we contained
the vampire offspring for study?

479
00:31:22,773 --> 00:31:24,570
We're assessing that situation.

480
00:31:24,773 --> 00:31:26,729
The same way you're assessing Angel.

481
00:31:26,933 --> 00:31:29,083
Why aren't we trying
to pinpoint Angel's location?

482
00:31:29,293 --> 00:31:31,853
Lilah, this is my corner of the sky.

483
00:31:32,053 --> 00:31:35,011
I decide when the sun rises
and when it sets.

484
00:31:35,213 --> 00:31:38,808
Lack of long-term vision has always
been one of your shortcomings.

485
00:31:39,013 --> 00:31:42,005
And lack of courage has always
been one of yours.

486
00:31:42,213 --> 00:31:45,523
You're afraid of Angel and his son.
And that's the reason...

487
00:31:45,693 --> 00:31:49,572
...for your daring strategy
of "wait and see," isn't it?

488
00:31:50,253 --> 00:31:53,404
You're afraid.
And fear breeds weakness.

489
00:31:53,893 --> 00:31:57,203
I'm hurt. Is that really
what you think of me?

490
00:31:57,413 --> 00:32:00,291
Yes. And Mr. Suvarta agrees with me.

491
00:32:01,973 --> 00:32:03,645
You spoke to a senior partner?

492
00:32:03,853 --> 00:32:07,892
He was really very helpful.
Had some great hints on office furniture.

493
00:32:08,093 --> 00:32:09,128
This is outrageous.

494
00:32:09,333 --> 00:32:11,642
Are you telling me
that you went over my head?

495
00:32:12,693 --> 00:32:13,762
[BEEPING]

496
00:32:16,653 --> 00:32:18,371
Just under it, actually.

497
00:32:23,973 --> 00:32:27,682
Mr. Suvarta didn't think Linwood's
corner of the sky was sunny enough.

498
00:32:28,093 --> 00:32:30,482
You're all reporting to me now.
Get out.

499
00:32:34,213 --> 00:32:35,202
Gavin.

500
00:32:37,093 --> 00:32:39,209
Please, remove that.

501
00:32:43,373 --> 00:32:44,408
[KNOCKING]

502
00:32:44,573 --> 00:32:47,246
- What?
- I brought you a snack.

503
00:32:48,733 --> 00:32:49,768
I'm not hungry.

504
00:32:51,173 --> 00:32:52,492
You're always hungry.

505
00:32:54,773 --> 00:32:56,843
- What is it?
- Bologna.

506
00:32:57,693 --> 00:32:58,682
No tomatoes?

507
00:32:59,453 --> 00:33:00,488
No tomatoes.

508
00:33:03,693 --> 00:33:06,082
- What do you say?
- Thank you.

509
00:33:06,333 --> 00:33:07,322
You're welcome.

510
00:33:14,293 --> 00:33:16,887
- Is he still mad?
- What do you think?

511
00:33:18,533 --> 00:33:19,522
Sorry.

512
00:33:22,173 --> 00:33:24,368
I can't imagine what you've
been through, Connor.

513
00:33:25,413 --> 00:33:28,928
Being taken away by Holtz,
raised in that place.

514
00:33:29,773 --> 00:33:31,286
It must have been horrible.

515
00:33:31,973 --> 00:33:34,885
I know you're still hurting.
But I promise...

516
00:33:35,053 --> 00:33:37,931
...it's not nearly as much
as you're gonna hurt...

517
00:33:38,093 --> 00:33:39,811
...for what you did to your father.

518
00:33:41,733 --> 00:33:43,325
[SCREAMING]

519
00:33:50,253 --> 00:33:52,687
FRED:
You think that's what Angel felt?

520
00:33:55,573 --> 00:33:59,168
When you did it to him,
did he scream like you?

521
00:33:59,613 --> 00:34:01,763
CONNOR: Why are you doing this?
- Don't even try.

522
00:34:02,453 --> 00:34:04,409
FRED:
We got a call from an old friend.

523
00:34:04,613 --> 00:34:05,887
Been playing a little Ahab.

524
00:34:06,053 --> 00:34:09,523
- He's out there right now on his boat.
- With Angel.

525
00:34:11,813 --> 00:34:13,565
That's right, Sparky,
Daddy's coming home.

526
00:34:13,773 --> 00:34:15,365
I guess there's gonna be a spanking.

527
00:34:15,533 --> 00:34:18,969
He's been down there all alone
for three months, and you knew.

528
00:34:19,173 --> 00:34:21,368
Is that what you did to Cordy?
Stuff her in a box?

529
00:34:21,533 --> 00:34:24,730
How could you do that to us?
We took you into our home...

530
00:34:24,933 --> 00:34:27,208
...we cared for you,
and all this time...

531
00:34:27,373 --> 00:34:30,365
How could you do that?
How could you...?

532
00:34:30,973 --> 00:34:31,962
GUNN:
Fred!

533
00:34:35,813 --> 00:34:37,724
[FRED SOBBING]

534
00:34:43,773 --> 00:34:45,729
JUSTINE:
He'll turn on you.

535
00:34:50,213 --> 00:34:53,046
He won't be able to help it.
That's what he is.

536
00:34:54,333 --> 00:34:58,042
Sooner or later, he will turn on
you and all your friends!

537
00:35:01,293 --> 00:35:02,567
You just going to leave me?

538
00:35:07,893 --> 00:35:11,488
You can continue being a slave,
Justine, or you can live your life.

539
00:35:12,173 --> 00:35:13,492
Your choice.

540
00:35:16,773 --> 00:35:19,128
FRED:
I would have done anything for him.

541
00:35:21,093 --> 00:35:23,971
Now all I want to do is hurt him.

542
00:35:24,613 --> 00:35:25,762
CONNOR:
Go ahead.

543
00:35:27,293 --> 00:35:29,249
- Hurt me some more, Fred.
- Shut up.

544
00:35:29,453 --> 00:35:31,842
You think I care?
You get used to it.

545
00:35:32,053 --> 00:35:35,284
You don't feel anything, do you?
There's nothing inside.

546
00:35:35,493 --> 00:35:37,211
Why don't you open me up
and find out?

547
00:35:37,413 --> 00:35:39,881
- How could you do it to your father?
- He's not my father.

548
00:35:40,093 --> 00:35:41,811
Yes, he is.

549
00:35:42,413 --> 00:35:43,926
He got what he deserved.

550
00:35:44,653 --> 00:35:47,645
And how soon before we deserved it?

551
00:35:52,493 --> 00:35:54,085
[DOOR OPENS]

552
00:35:58,253 --> 00:35:59,845
I believe you're looking for this.

553
00:36:00,053 --> 00:36:01,771
Angel.

554
00:36:03,773 --> 00:36:05,252
- My God.
- Is he gonna be all right?

555
00:36:05,413 --> 00:36:07,210
WESLEY:
In time. Maybe.

556
00:36:07,373 --> 00:36:08,647
[ANGEL GROANING]

557
00:36:09,093 --> 00:36:10,651
GUNN: He's out of it.
FRED: Oh, God.

558
00:36:10,853 --> 00:36:12,252
GUNN: It's okay.
FRED: Look.

559
00:36:12,413 --> 00:36:13,971
GUNN:
He's gonna be okay.

560
00:36:14,133 --> 00:36:18,809
What do we do? Wesley...
Where are you going?

561
00:36:21,573 --> 00:36:22,562
I'm done here.

562
00:36:22,773 --> 00:36:24,411
Why take so long
to tell us about him?

563
00:36:24,613 --> 00:36:26,046
You knew what he could do to us.

564
00:36:26,253 --> 00:36:28,244
You're human.
He wouldn't have hurt you.

565
00:36:28,413 --> 00:36:30,051
I thought you were safer
not knowing.

566
00:36:30,213 --> 00:36:34,525
We were safer? You really
don't care anymore, do you?

567
00:36:41,093 --> 00:36:45,052
He'll need more blood. I'm fresh out.

568
00:36:48,493 --> 00:36:50,131
[ANGEL GROANS]

569
00:36:50,293 --> 00:36:51,282
FRED:
It's okay.

570
00:36:52,013 --> 00:36:54,481
- God, he's freezing.
- I'll get some more blankets.

571
00:36:54,693 --> 00:36:56,092
[CLATTERING]

572
00:36:56,493 --> 00:36:57,767
FRED:
Connor.

573
00:37:04,333 --> 00:37:05,891
[SCREAMS]

574
00:37:10,493 --> 00:37:11,812
Sit...

575
00:37:12,093 --> 00:37:13,572
...down.

576
00:37:20,573 --> 00:37:22,052
You're too weak to take me.

577
00:37:23,173 --> 00:37:24,572
You really think that?

578
00:37:45,093 --> 00:37:46,082
So...

579
00:37:47,693 --> 00:37:48,762
...how was your summer?

580
00:37:50,253 --> 00:37:51,811
Mine was fun.

581
00:37:52,013 --> 00:37:56,370
Saw fish. Went mad with hunger.
Hallucinated a whole bunch.

582
00:37:56,973 --> 00:37:58,326
You deserve worse.

583
00:37:58,533 --> 00:38:00,967
Because I killed Holtz. Except I didn't.

584
00:38:01,893 --> 00:38:04,805
I tried telling you that while you
were busy offshore dumping me...

585
00:38:05,013 --> 00:38:07,083
...but I didn't know the whole score.

586
00:38:09,373 --> 00:38:10,886
Holtz killed himself.

587
00:38:12,093 --> 00:38:16,484
Actually, he had your buddy Justine
do it with an ice pick...

588
00:38:16,693 --> 00:38:18,604
...just to make you hate me.

589
00:38:20,013 --> 00:38:21,412
Even if...

590
00:38:23,773 --> 00:38:27,322
- You still deserved it.
- What I deserve is open to debate.

591
00:38:28,853 --> 00:38:30,889
But understand,
there's a difference between...

592
00:38:31,053 --> 00:38:34,443
...wishing vengeance on someone
and taking it.

593
00:38:37,573 --> 00:38:40,645
So now the question becomes...

594
00:38:43,253 --> 00:38:44,891
...what do you deserve?

595
00:38:50,213 --> 00:38:51,851
Daddy's not finished talking.

596
00:38:57,773 --> 00:38:59,968
Wesley told me everything
that's been going on.

597
00:39:00,453 --> 00:39:04,412
So as far as I'm concerned,
what you deserve rests on one answer.

598
00:39:06,733 --> 00:39:08,644
Did you do something to Cordelia?

599
00:39:09,613 --> 00:39:10,887
No.

600
00:39:11,053 --> 00:39:12,452
- He's lying.
- No, I'm not.

601
00:39:12,613 --> 00:39:14,763
GUNN: Just happened to disappear
the same night.

602
00:39:14,933 --> 00:39:17,288
I'm telling the truth, okay?

603
00:39:17,693 --> 00:39:18,682
I know.

604
00:39:21,333 --> 00:39:22,971
I can tell.

605
00:39:23,173 --> 00:39:25,607
Done enough lying
for me to know the difference.

606
00:39:26,253 --> 00:39:27,845
The truth has a better sound to it.

607
00:39:28,053 --> 00:39:29,202
Less nasal, you know?

608
00:39:31,973 --> 00:39:32,962
Get up.

609
00:39:40,693 --> 00:39:43,730
What you did to me was unbelievable,
Connor.

610
00:39:46,053 --> 00:39:48,362
I got stuck in a hell dimension
by my girlfriend...

611
00:39:48,533 --> 00:39:51,331
...for a hundred years,
so a few months under the ocean...

612
00:39:51,493 --> 00:39:53,006
...actually gave me perspective.

613
00:39:53,653 --> 00:39:56,725
Kind of a M.C. Escher perspective.

614
00:39:58,253 --> 00:39:59,811
But I did get time to think.

615
00:40:01,173 --> 00:40:04,006
About us. About the world.

616
00:40:06,653 --> 00:40:08,962
Nothing in the world is the way
it ought to be.

617
00:40:10,573 --> 00:40:13,451
It's harsh and cruel.

618
00:40:13,653 --> 00:40:15,530
But that's why there's us.

619
00:40:17,453 --> 00:40:18,488
Champions.

620
00:40:19,813 --> 00:40:21,371
Doesn't matter
where we come from...

621
00:40:21,573 --> 00:40:23,450
...what we've
done or suffered...

622
00:40:23,653 --> 00:40:25,484
...or even if we
make a difference.

623
00:40:25,653 --> 00:40:29,692
We live as though the world were as
it should be to show it what it can be.

624
00:40:33,213 --> 00:40:35,283
You're not a part of that yet.

625
00:40:35,933 --> 00:40:37,730
I hope you will be.

626
00:40:47,653 --> 00:40:49,484
I love you, Connor.

627
00:40:52,973 --> 00:40:55,441
Now, get out of my house.

628
00:41:04,693 --> 00:41:06,092
Angel!

629
00:41:07,653 --> 00:41:10,121
All that talking, it really
takes it out of you.

630
00:41:10,613 --> 00:41:14,128
FRED: He needs rest.
- I need Cordy. Now.

631
00:41:14,693 --> 00:41:17,890
Wherever she is,
whatever she's going through.

632
00:41:19,133 --> 00:41:20,964
We have to find her.

633
00:41:31,853 --> 00:41:34,242
God, I am so bored.

634
00:42:12,493 --> 00:42:13,482
Subtitles by
SDI Media Group

635
00:42:13,653 --> 00:42:14,642
[ENGLISH SDH]

